HEADWORD: Malthus
<hw>Malthus</hw> <pos>prop. n.</pos> <def>Thomas Robert Malthus, an
English economist who argued that increases in population would outgrow
increases in the means of subsistence (1766-1834).</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> Thomas Malthus, Thomas Robert Malthus.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Malthusian</ent>⟦br⟧
